1) 

yeet = ("hello", 12)

def function(name, age):
    print(age)
    print(name)

function(yeet)

Doesn't work, it requires 2 pieces of data separately. Tuples don't work as an argument with functions.

2)

A pair would be a generalization of a tuple as tuples can have more than 2 pieces of data.

3)

A pair is a kind of tuple, Tuples can have more than two pieces of data. 
